com.intel.icecp.scheduler.schedule

Interface Schedule

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    QuartzSchedule

    public interface Schedule
    Interface for schedule objects, which handle the scheduling and firing of triggers.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

    • Method Detail

      • start

        boolean start()
        Start the schedule. All triggers that have been added to the schedule will be active.
        Returns:
        True if the schedule successfully started, false otherwise.

      • suspend

        boolean suspend()
        Suspend the schedule. All triggers associated with this schedule will be suspended and will not fire.
        Returns:
        True if the schedule successfully suspended, false otherwise.

      • resume

        boolean resume()
        Resume the schedule. All triggers associated with this schedule will resume and be active.
        Returns:
        True if the schedule successfully resumed, false otherwise.

      • stop

        boolean stop()
        Stop the schedule. All triggers associated with this schedule will be deleted.
        Returns:
        True if the schedule successfully stopped, false otherwise.

      • checkJobExists

        boolean checkJobExists(String triggerId,
                       String triggerGroup)
        Check if trigger exists in the schedule
        Parameters:
        triggerId - the trigger id
        triggerGroup - the trigger group
        Returns:
        true if exists, else false

      • scheduleRangeTrigger

        void scheduleRangeTrigger(RangeTrigger trigger,
                          String creatorName)
        Add a trigger to the schedule. Triggers are considered unique by their ID, which can be obtained with the BaseTrigger.getId() method.
        Parameters:
        trigger - range trigger to add to the schedule.
        creatorName - Additional metadata that indicates originator of the trigger being created.

      • scheduleIntervalTrigger

        void scheduleIntervalTrigger(IntervalTrigger trigger,
                             String creatorName)
        Add a trigger to the schedule. Triggers are considered unique by their ID, which can be obtained with the BaseTrigger.getId() method.
        Parameters:
        trigger - interval trigger to add to the schedule.
        creatorName - Additional metadata that indicates originator of the trigger being created.
